<subSubSection id="E0B66549FFBE2857FF1DF9742AEDA4B4" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A81336C2FFBE2857FF1DF9742AEDA4B4" blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1957]" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">
<emphasis id="9AD8EAD0FFBE2857FF1DF9742F4AA5B7" bold="true" box="[199,335,1677,1702]" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">Comments.</emphasis>
Because of the maculated wings, 
<taxonomicName id="6FAC4D41FFBE2857FD0FF9762D92A5B7" authority="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael, 2018" authorityName="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2018" box="[725,919,1678,1702]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferreirai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="9AD8EAD0FFBE2857FD0FF9762D92A5B7" box="[725,919,1678,1702]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">Bittacus ferreirai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="9AD8EAD0FFBE2857FC7AF9742DE5A5B7" bold="true" box="[928,992,1677,1702]" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="81EB57ABFFBE2857FC7AF9742DE5A5B7" box="[928,992,1677,1702]" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is another species that would fit in the “group 
<taxonomicName id="6FAC4D41FFBE2857FF36F94B2F4BA5DA" authorityName="Klug" authorityYear="1838" box="[236,334,1714,1739]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chilensis">
<emphasis id="9AD8EAD0FFBE2857FF36F94B2F4BA5DA" box="[236,334,1714,1739]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">chilensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” as proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="CC3D4B33FFBE2857FDCFF94B2D4BA5DB" author="Collucci, E. &amp; Amorim, D. S." box="[533,846,1714,1739]" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref14802" refString="Collucci, E. &amp; Amorim, D. S. (2000) Three new species of Thyridates Navas, 1908 (Mecoptera, Bittacidae) from Brazil, with new combinations and some comments about phylogenetic relationships within the genus. Contribuicoes Avulsas Sobre a Historia Natural do Brasil, Serie Zoologia, 21, 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="2000">Collucci &amp; Amorim (2000)</bibRefCitation>
. Within the group, 
<taxonomicName id="6FAC4D41FFBE2857FBF3F94A2AA2A5DB" authorityName="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2018" box="[1065,1191,1714,1738]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferreirai">
<emphasis id="9AD8EAD0FFBE2857FBF3F94A2AA2A5DB" box="[1065,1191,1714,1738]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">B. ferreirai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be closer to 
<taxonomicName id="6FAC4D41FFBE2857FF4DF92E2F1BA5FF" authorityName=": Pictet" authorityYear="1836" box="[151,286,1749,1774]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blancheti">
<emphasis id="9AD8EAD0FFBE2857FF4DF92E2F1BA5FF" box="[151,286,1749,1774]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">B. blancheti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the male epandrium of both species does not present any actiniform process and the internal margins of the lobes converge towards the apex. However, they can be easily separated by the general shape and color of the wings. Based on the wing shape and body color, 
<taxonomicName id="6FAC4D41FFBE2857FD1BF8E62D3AA427" authority="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael, 2018" authorityName="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2018" box="[705,831,1822,1846]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferreirai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="9AD8EAD0FFBE2857FD1BF8E62D3AA427" box="[705,831,1822,1846]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">B. ferreirai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="81EB57ABFFBE2857FC9CF8E42D82A427" box="[838,903,1821,1846]" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" rank="species">
<emphasis id="9AD8EAD0FFBE2857FC9CF8E42D82A427" bold="true" box="[838,903,1821,1846]" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="6FAC4D41FFBE2857FBC6F8E62A71A427" authority="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael, 2018" authorityName="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2018" box="[1052,1140,1823,1846]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cruzi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="9AD8EAD0FFBE2857FBC6F8E62A71A427" box="[1052,1140,1823,1846]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">B. cruzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="9AD8EAD0FFBE2857FBA1F8E42AB9A427" bold="true" box="[1147,1212,1821,1846]" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="81EB57ABFFBE2857FBA1F8E42AB9A427" box="[1147,1212,1821,1846]" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(1 costal crossvein, Rs 
<subScript id="34283487FFBE2857FF6EF8A82EC9A44E" attach="left" box="[180,204,1873,1887]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">1+2</subScript>
not forked in the hind wing and legs and antennae not alternating between pale and dark bands), but their head color, mostly pale in 
<taxonomicName id="6FAC4D41FFBE2857FE4DF8932C1CA490" authorityName="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2018" box="[407,537,1897,1921]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferreirai">
<emphasis id="9AD8EAD0FFBE2857FE4DF8932C1CA490" box="[407,537,1897,1921]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">B. ferreirai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, mostly dark brown in 
<emphasis id="9AD8EAD0FFBE2857FCE2F8932D9EA490" box="[824,923,1898,1921]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">
<taxonomicName id="6FAC4D41FFBE2857FCE2F8932D92A490" authorityName="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2018" box="[824,919,1898,1921]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cruzi">B. cruzi</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and male genitalia with internal margin of epandrium converging in 
<taxonomicName id="6FAC4D41FFBE2857FE6DF8772C31A4B4" authorityName="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2018" box="[439,564,1933,1957]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferreirai">
<emphasis id="9AD8EAD0FFBE2857FE6DF8772C31A4B4" box="[439,564,1933,1957]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">B. ferreirai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and diverging posteriorly in 
<emphasis id="9AD8EAD0FFBE2857FCA3F8772DD2A4B5" box="[889,983,1933,1957]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">
<taxonomicName id="6FAC4D41FFBE2857FCA3F8772DD6A4B5" authorityName="Machado &amp; Mendes &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2018" box="[889,979,1933,1957]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cruzi">B. cruzi</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
easily distinguish them.
</paragraph>
